The paper discusses the implementation of a numerical method, the successive overrelaxation method, on reconfigurable hardware. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-category, as it discusses hardware implementation. The paper may also be relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category, as the hardware implementation may involve parallel processing. The paper may also be relevant to the modeling and simulation (cs.MS) sub-category, as it discusses the implementation of a numerical method for simulation purposes. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category, as it discusses the implementation of a numerical method in software.
